</dl>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@KJ{{five^grade}} verbs form the imperative by changing the final kana to the @HI{{e}}-row.
</p>

<p>
@KJ{{ichi^grade}} verbs form the imperative by dropping the final @HI{{ru}}
and adding the suffix @HI{{ro}}.
</p>

<p>
The two irregular verbs conjugate as shown above.
</p>


<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
Non-volitional verbs, such as @HI{{wakaru}}, @HI{{dekiru}} and @HI{{aru}}, do not have prohibitive forms.
</p>

